UCSF Gene Subset¶

The UCSF500 is a ~500 gene subset that will ideally provide similar dimensionality reduction results as if using the entire protein-coding gene set (20k genes).

In [30]:
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import holoviews as hv
from collections import defaultdict

from progressbar import ProgressBar

import rnaseq_lib as r

hv.extension('bokeh')

Collect t-ETE Plots¶

In [115]:
%%time
# Pick a subset of tissues to examine
tissues = ['Adrenal', 'Bladder', 'Breast', 'Kidney', 'Lung', 'Liver']

# Create dictionary to store results
info = defaultdict(dict)

# Create a "template" dataframe to build off of
temp = met[['id', 'sex', 'tissue', 'dataset', 'tumor', 'type']].drop_duplicates()

# Create output directory for pandas dataframes if it doesn't exist
r.utils.mkdir_p('pandas')

# Iterate and run t-ETE
bar = ProgressBar()
for tissue in bar(sorted(tissues)):
    samples = [x for x in met[met.tissue == tissue].id.unique() if x in df.columns]
    
    # Run t-ETE for protein-coding genes
    name = 'pandas/{}-pc.pandas'.format(tissue)
    try:
        info[tissue]['pc'] = pd.read_pickle(name)
    except IOError:
        pc = r.dim_red.run_tete(df[samples].T)
        info[tissue]['pc'] = pd.concat([temp.loc[samples], pd.DataFrame(pc, columns=['x', 'y'], index=samples)], axis=1)
        info[tissue]['pc'].to_pickle(name)
    
    # Run t-ETE for UCSF500 genes
    name = 'pandas/{}-ucsf.pandas'.format(tissue)
    try:
        info[tissue]['ucsf'] = pd.read_pickle(name)
    except IOError:        
        ucsf = r.dim_red.run_tete(ucsf_df[samples].T)
        info[tissue]['ucsf'] = pd.concat([temp.loc[samples], pd.DataFrame(ucsf, columns=['x', 'y'], index=samples)], axis=1)
        info[tissue]['ucsf'].to_pickle(name)

Convert dataframes to plots

In [116]:
plots = defaultdict(dict)
for tissue in info:
    for s in info[tissue]:
        plots[tissue][s] = hv.Scatter(data=info[tissue][s], kdims=['x'], 
                                      vdims=['y', 'type', 'tissue', 'tumor', 'dataset', 'sex', 'id'], 
                                      group=tissue + '-' + s)

Tuning Number of Neighbors¶

In [236]:
adrenal_plots = {}
tissue = 'Adrenal'
samples = [x for x in met[met.tissue == tissue].id.unique() if x in ucsf_df.columns]

bar = ProgressBar()
for i in bar(xrange(10, 100, 20)):
    z = r.dim_red.run_tete(ucsf_df[samples].T, num_neighbors=i)
    temp_df = pd.concat([temp.loc[samples], pd.DataFrame(z, columns=['x', 'y'], index=samples)], axis=1) 
    adrenal_plots[i] = hv.Scatter(data=temp_df, kdims=['x'], 
                                      vdims=['y', 'type', 'tissue', 'tumor', 'dataset', 'sex', 'id'], 
                                      group='num_neighbors: {}'.format(i))
